type: web_research
title: Crypto Sentiment Analysis & NLP-Based Crash Prediction Comprehensive Research
key_insights[20]: "Fear & Greed Index: 0-100 scale, components = Volatility 25%, Momentum/Volume 25%, Social Media 15%, BTC Dominance 10%, Google Trends 10%","LunarCrush: Galaxy Score + AltRank, crypto-specific NLP, tracks 4000+ topics","Santiment: on-chain + social + dev data, 4300+ cryptos, MVRV/NVT ratios","The TIE: institutional-grade, 500+ tokens since 2017, minute-level granularity","Token Metrics: Twitter/Reddit/Telegram, polarity -1 to +1, tiered pricing","FinBERT: F1 0.85-0.93 on financial text, 88% accuracy baseline","CryptoBERT: +19% improvement over FinBERT for crypto-specific tasks","Fine-tuned GPT-4 outperforms base GPT-4, BERT, FinBERT in crypto sentiment","FinBERT-BiLSTM: 98% BTC accuracy, 97% ETH accuracy for price prediction","MVRV Z-Score: 90%+ accuracy for cycle top detection within 2 weeks","NUPL > 0.75 = Euphoria/tops, NUPL < 0 = Capitulation/bottoms","Whale Alert: 3.58% abnormal return within 2 minutes of tweet, 44% BTC volume increase in 24h","Exchange inflows: whales account for 45% of inflows as crash warning","October 2025 crash: $3.21B liquidated in 60 seconds, $9.89B total, funding rates rose from 10% to 30%","CryptoQuant Bull Score: 80 at BTC peak $126K, dropped to 0 post-crash",SNR filtering improves sentiment-volatility correlation to r=0.37,Bot accounts estimated at 15-18% of crypto tweets,24% of tokens launched in 2022 showed pump-and-dump characteristics,Sentiment-based prediction more accurate for crypto than traditional stocks,"LLM nowcasting benchmarks: Gemini 2.5 Pro leads, followed by GPT-4.1"
findings[10]: Crypto Fear & Greed Index currently at 6 (Extreme Fear) as of Feb 2026,"BTC ATH was $126,080 on Oct 6, 2025, now trading below $68K",ML models achieve 70-91% accuracy predicting crypto price movements from sentiment extremes,Elon Musk tweets cause 3.58% abnormal return within 2 minutes,NLP data integration improves forecasting accuracy by 3% and profits by 20%,BART MNLI zero-shot classification outperforms dictionary-based sentiment methods,"October 2025 crash: 86x acceleration in liquidation rate during cascade",CryptoQuant exchange flow metrics correctly flagged late-2025 bearish shift,MVRV above 3.2 occurs only 6% of trading days (extreme overvaluation),Funding rates above 10% annualized signal elevated liquidation risk
recommendations[7]: Use multi-indicator frameworks combining sentiment + on-chain + derivatives data,Implement SNR filtering and bot detection before acting on sentiment signals,"Monitor MVRV Z-Score, NUPL, exchange inflows, and funding rates as composite crash warning system",Use CryptoBERT over vanilla FinBERT for crypto-specific sentiment tasks,Combine LLM-based analysis with traditional NLP for context-aware sentiment detection,Track long/short ratios across multiple exchanges for divergence signals,Implement multi-timeframe analysis to filter short-term noise
